ms not just to inform but also to ensure that your preparedness translates into safety and well-being for the children under your care.</span>
</p></div></div></div></div></div><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Previous" class="pf-slider-prev none hide"></button><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Next" class="pf-slider-next none hide"></button></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-5208" data-category="Collection Suggestion" data-name="Tea" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-dBFCZX khzvmY pf-22_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-gvPcJq dRaLso"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-23_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-24_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-25_ pf-heading-1-h3">Importance of a paediatric first aid kit
</h3><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-27_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Every year, approximately one million children in the UK find themselves in emergency departments due to accidents at home or in school settings. These situations can range from minor injuries to life-threatening emergencies. The first few minutes after an accident are critical in determining the outcomes for a child. A well-stocked paediatric first aid kit can make the difference between a swift recovery and long-term consequences.










</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-29_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-30_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-31_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-33_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-34_ pf-text-1"><strong>Paediatric first aid kit </strong>- A collection of medical supplies and equipment specifically designed to administer first aid to infants and children.


















</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-36_ pf-text-1"><strong>First aid</strong> - The initial assistance or treatment given to a casualty for any injury or sudden illness before the arrival of qualified medical assistance.

















</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-38_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-39_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-40_ pf-heading-1-h3">Relevant legislation and regulations</h3><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-42_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">In the UK, the Health and Safety (First-Aid) Regulations 1981 require employers to provide adequate and appropriate equipment, facilities, and personnel to ensure their employees receive immediate attention if they are injured or taken ill at work. The guidance extends to environments where children are present, notably in educational settings and childcare provisions under the purview of the Early Years Foundation Stage (EYFS).
<br><br>Furthermore, the Care Quality Commission (CQC) highlights the necessity of having appropriate first aid training and resources when caring for children. This includes having a paediatric first aid kit readily accessible and maintained.
<br>











</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-44_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-45_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-46_ pf-heading-1-h3">Essential contents of a paediatric first aid kit</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-48_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-49_ pf-text-1"><strong>Adhesive bandages and dressings</strong> - Various sizes, suitable for covering small cuts, blisters, and wounds.
















</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-51_ pf-text-1"><strong>Sterile gauze pads and rolls</strong> - For dressing larger wounds and providing support for sprains and strains.

















</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-53_ pf-text-1"><strong>Antiseptic wipes and creams </strong>- To clean wounds and prevent infection.


















</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-55_ pf-text-1"><strong>Burn gel and dressings</strong> - Specific to paediatric use, these should be suitable for treating minor burns.



















</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-57_ pf-text-1"><strong>Saline solution</strong> - For cleaning wounds or washing out dirt or foreign bodies from the eyes.



















</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-59_ pf-text-1"><strong>Thermometer</strong> - Preferably digital, for checking body temperature.




















</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-61_ pf-text-1"><strong>Child-safe scissors and tweezers </strong>- For cutting bandages or removing small foreign objects.





















</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-63_ pf-text-1"><strong>Ice packs</strong> - Disposable or reusable, essential for bumps, bruises, or swelling.






















</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-65_ pf-text-1"><strong>Nitrile gloves</strong> - To prevent contamination and protect the first aider.























</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-67_ pf-text-1"><strong>Resuscitation face shield or mask</strong> - With a one-way valve, for safe administration of CPR.























</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-69_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-70_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-71_ pf-heading-1-h3">Best practices for using and maintaining your kit</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-73_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-74_ pf-text-1">Regularly check and replace expired or used items.













</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-76_ pf-text-1">Tailor the kit's contents to the specific age group of children under your care.
















</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-78_ pf-text-1">Ensure everyone responsible for child care is familiar with the kit's components and their uses.


















</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-80_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-81_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-82_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommendations for training and awareness</h3><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-84_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Alongside a well-equipped first aid kit, proper training in paediatric first aid is indispensable. It is recommended that all childcare providers undertake a paediatric first aid course, which is regularly updated to keep pace with best practices and new guidelines.













